org.apache.freemarker.servlet

Class IncludePage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.freemarker.servlet.IncludePage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TemplateCallableModel, TemplateDirectiveModel, TemplateModel

    public class IncludePage
extends Object
implements TemplateDirectiveModel
    A model that when invoked with a 'path' parameter will perform a servlet include. It also support an optional hash named 'params' which specifies request parameters for the include - its keys are strings, its values should be either strings or sequences of strings (for multiple valued parameters). A third optional parameter 'inherit_params' should be a boolean when specified, and it defaults to true when not specified. A value of true means that the include inherits the request parameters from the current request. In this case values in 'params' will get prepended to the existing values of parameters.

        Invokes the directive.

        execute in interface TemplateDirectiveModel
        Parameters:
        args - The array of argument values. Not null. If a parameter was omitted on the caller side, the corresponding array element will be null. The length of the array and the indexes correspond to the ArgumentArrayLayout returned by TemplateDirectiveModel.getDirectiveArgumentArrayLayout(). ArgumentArrayLayout os not nullm and the caller doesn't keep argument layout rules (such as the array is shorter than ArgumentArrayLayout.getTotalLength(), or the type of the values at ArgumentArrayLayout.getPositionalVarargsArgumentIndex() or at ArgumentArrayLayout.getNamedVarargsArgumentIndex() is improper), this method may throws IndexOutOfBoundsException or ClassCastException. Thus, user Java code that wishes to call TemplateCallableModel-s is responsible to ensure that the argument array follows the layout described be ArgumentArrayLayout, as the execute method isn't meant to do validations on that level.
        callPlace - The place (in a template, normally) where this directive was called from. Not null; in case the call is not from a template, you can use NonTemplateCallPlace.INSTANCE (or another NonTemplateCallPlace instance). Note that CallPlace.executeNestedContent(TemplateModel[], Writer, Environment) can be used to execute the nested content (even if there's no nested content; then simply nothing happens), and to pass nested content parameters to it.
        out - Print the output here (if there's any)
        env - The current processing environment. Not null in general, though certain implementations may specifically allow that, typically, implementations that are just adapters towards FreeMarker-unaware callables (for example, JavaMethodModel is like that).
        Throws:
        TemplateException - If any problem occurs that's not an IOException during writing the template output.
        IOException - When writing the template output fails.

      • getDirectiveArgumentArrayLayout

        public ArgumentArrayLayout getDirectiveArgumentArrayLayout()
        Description copied from interface: TemplateDirectiveModel
        Returns the argument array layout to use when calling the {@link #execute(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Writer, Environment)} method, or rarely null. If it's null then there can only be positional arguments, any number of them (though of course the execute method implementation itself may restricts the acceptable argument count), and the argument array will be simply as long as the number of arguments specified at the call place.

        getDirectiveArgumentArrayLayout in interface TemplateDirectiveModel

      • isNestedContentSupported

        public boolean isNestedContentSupported()
        Description copied from interface: TemplateDirectiveModel
        Tells if this directive supports having nested content. If false, yet the caller specifies a non-empty nested content (non-0-length, even whitespace matters), FreeMarker will throw a TemplateException with descriptive error message, and TemplateDirectiveModel.execute(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Writer, Environment) won't be called. If true, the author of the directive shouldn't forget calling CallPlace.executeNestedContent(TemplateModel[], Writer, Environment), unless the intent was to skip the nested content. (This property was added to prevent the frequent oversight (in FreeMarker 2) where a directive that isn't supposed to have nested content doesn't examine if there's a nested content to throw an exception in that case. Then if there's nested content, it will be silently skipped during execution, as the directive never calls CallPlace.executeNestedContent(TemplateModel[], Writer, Environment).)
        Specified by:
        isNestedContentSupported in interface TemplateDirectiveModel
